def convert(s, numRows):
    if numRows == 1 or numRows >= len(s):
        return s

    rows = [""] * numRows
    cur_row = 0
    going_down = False

    for c in s:
        rows[cur_row] += c
        if cur_row == 0 or cur_row == numRows - 1:
            going_down = not going_down
        cur_row += 1 if going_down else -1

    return "".join(rows)
Simulate the zigzag directly: walk down rows 0..numRows-1, bounce back up at the edges, appending each character to its current row's buffer, then concatenate all rows. O(n) time, O(n) space.

