def isValid(s):
    stack = []
    pairs = {")": "(", "]": "[", "}": "{"}
    for c in s:
        if c in "([{":
            stack.append(c)
        elif c in pairs:
            if not stack or stack.pop() != pairs[c]:
                return False
    return not stack
Push opening brackets onto a stack; on a closing bracket, it must match the top of the stack (the most recent unmatched opener). If the stack is empty at a closing bracket, or non-empty at the end, the string is invalid. O(n) time, O(n) space.

